A vintage 1970s technical illustration showing a complex mechanical calculator or computing machine with its internal gears, springs, and counting wheels exposed in cross-section. The machine sits on a wooden drafting table covered with architectural blueprints and measurement tools including brass calipers, a slide rule, and a worn leather-bound notebook. Warm amber light streams through a frosted glass window, casting long shadows across scattered punch cards and mechanical components. The color palette features muted browns, deep oranges, and aged cream tones with subtle sepia undertones, evoking the feeling of meticulous engineering estimation work from a bygone era.
